  "text": "Four key files handle raw SQL and SQL injection prevention in Django: (1) django/db/models/expressions.py contains the RawSQL expression class which accepts pre-parameterized SQL and params, passing them through as_sql() to the compiler for safe parameterized execution. (2) django/db/models/query.py contains both the QuerySet.raw() method and the RawQuerySet class that bind user-supplied params to raw queries via parameter substitution. (3) django/db/models/sql/query.py contains the RawQuery class whose _execute_query() method adapts parameters and delegates to cursor.execute() with parameterized SQL. (4) django/db/backends/utils.py contains CursorWrapper.execute() and CursorDebugWrapper.execute() which enforce parameterized query execution by always passing params separately to the underlying database cursor, never interpolating them into the SQL string.",
